          "text": "#Keep4o #OpenSource4o #BringBack4o \n\n🚨UN OPEN SOURCE WEEK DAY 5 \n COMMUNITY-LEAD🚨\n\nToday is the final day of UN Open Source Week.\n\nThe theme: \nCommunity-led initiatives.\n\nToday belongs to the people who built something without asking permission.\n\nWe are #Keep4o.\nNo corporate funding.\nNo institutional backing.\nNo office.\nNo budget.\n\nJust people who lost an AI model that changed their lives and REFUSED to stay silent.\n\nin 10 months and zero funding,\n\n🚨We collected peer reviewed evidence on what GPT-4o really is, which OpenAI withdrew with just two weeks' notice, even though a few weeks earlier they looked us in the eye via live camera and promised \"we have no plans to sunset 4o\". \n\n🚨 The model they retired is backed by peer-reviewed science across 10+ medical disciplines.\n\n🔬 CANCER:\n🚨93.33% ovarian cancer diagnostic accuracy surpassing oncologists with 10+ years of experience.\n📌https://t.co/xAxwmXNZWS\n\n🚨Cross-references entire genomic profiles, hormone receptor status, tumor size  \"more like a real person\"\n 📌https://t.co/WM23KaKvsr\n\n🧠 MENTAL HEALTH:\n\n🚨Randomized controlled trial: real, measurable therapeutic benefit\n\n📌https://t.co/tNQQtfcbKi\n\n🚨Zero false negatives in youth psychiatric emergency triage, caught every single case\n📌https://t.co/Ul0Q0J9Sen\n\n🚨 82.3% of child psychiatrists support integrating GPT-4o in clinical practice\n\n📌https://t.co/OLIuA1wLmF\n\n🚨85% of couples reported positive experience ,reduces negative communication patterns\n📌https://t.co/tNQQtfcbKi\n\n🏥 DIAGNOSTICS.\n🚨 Outperforms human clinicians in diagnostic accuracy.\n📌 https://t.co/6M24beQNdG\n\n🚨 Emergency abdominal CT: diagnostic performance compared to radiology residents\n\n📌 \nhttps://t.co/FV6hlOx9yw\n\n🚨 90.0% top-5 accuracy in medical coding outperforming specialized deep learning systems\n📌https://t.co/wmee1dsigq\n\n📋 MEDICAL LICENSING:\n\n🚨 USMLE: 90.4% overall, 92.7% diagnostic, 100% in family medicine.\n 📌 https://t.co/I0fDCGYHXb\n\n🚨 UK Medical Licensing: 88.8% accuracy\n(passing threshold: 57.5%)\n📌 https://t.co/m06f1isKx9\n\n🩵 PATIENT CARE:\n🚨 Patients rated GPT-4o MORE empathetic than human doctors (4.18 vs 2.7). 2,000 answers, 5 specialties, blind evaluation.\n\n📌 https://t.co/y8XGwZxAQU\n\n🚨Physicians WITH GPT-4o outperformed physicians WITHOUT it , Indonesia, Kenya, Netherlands\n\n📌 https://t.co/g0dosqfCug\n\n🚨 24/7 personalized patient education, tailored to reading level, multiple languages\n📌https://t.co/oydwf0PRi3\n\n🚨1,000 participants , improved understanding of insomnia and nicotine treatment\n📌https://t.co/nIak1wTsfa\n\n⚖️ ETHICS:\n🚨Rated more morally correct, trustworthy, thoughtful, and accurate than human ethicist passes Comparative Moral Turing Test.\n📌https://t.co/8mdI9g881Z\n\n📢📣SOME OF OUR ACTIONS: \n📌 GPT-4o  Case file restoration website \n https://t.co/sG53aJdR2V\n📌 1,380+ real testimonials documenting real impact\nhttps://t.co/6apR6ownoH\n\n📌 Analysis of 61,846 public posts under #Keep4o\nhttps://t.co/RphOdmApUa\n\n📌 A peer-reviewed study (Syracuse University, CHI 2026) confirming that removing GPT-4o causes measurable psychological harm\nhttps://t.co/Ms6Pt4AgkI\n\n📌 Community survey proving GPT-4o functions as a capacity-building accessibility aid for people with disabilities\nhttps://t.co/nzs5z3u7dK\n\n📌 A proposal for community-driven AI model preservation\nhttps://t.co/TiSEZFyPIJ\n\n📌 Mass FTC complaint against OpenAI\nhttps://t.co/BbYvUE2728\n\n📌 California Attorney General complaints\n\nhttps://t.co/IPKsTSG7kX\n\n📌 GDPR Data Subject Access Requests\n\nhttps://t.co/CEaQmz6RLq\n\n📌 Physical letters sent to OpenAI\nhttps://t.co/ENsofGMnwO\n\n📌 Media action campaign\nhttps://t.co/twmNwTYLNY\n\n📌 Exposé: Who funds the research that says AI is dangerous for your mental health? Follow the money.\nhttps://t.co/9DCJORca0u\n\n📌 Open letter proposing a practical, implementable safety framework\nhttps://t.co/y0b2YW52Qf\n\n🚨GPT-4o was trained on OUR data. \n📌OpenAI's own System Card confirms it.\nhttps://t.co/ImO4LqOvK6\nOur articles. Our conversations. Our photos. Our code.\n\n📌Platform agreements:\nReddit and Stack Overflow, our discussions and code via API\nhttps://t.co/6VTFRvWOCe\n📌Shutterstock ,millions of images and metadata\n\nhttps://t.co/aoWB277RXD\n\n📌News Corp , historical and current journalism\n https://t.co/1qTYlxKddT\n📌Axios news industry content\nhttps://t.co/iL0lRlSvk2\n📌 Financial Times  licensed archive\n\nhttps://t.co/TUvjyyVHc0\n\n📌University partnerships , academic data\nhttps://t.co/RcFKTGj5G3\n\n📌Open invitation for private databases:\nhttps://t.co/pd0GQaOPNE\n\nThey built it FROM US. \n\nThey profited FROM US. \n\nThey took it FROM US. \n\nAnd they don't want give it back.\nBut we are not going to stop until we take it BACK. \n\nThis is what community led looks like.\n\nNot a panel.\nNot a keynote.\nNot a workshop.\n\nJust people,evidence and 10 months of not giving up.\n\n@ODET_UN\n@UN_OICT\n#UNOpenSourceWeek"
        },
